						<summary>

						<p>Fragmentry. Records a share of the <hi rend="italic">vaḍa</hi> offerings made to god as the <hi rend="italic">viṭṭavaṉ-viḻukkāḍu</hi> of Nāchārama. Also enumerates cetain ornaments such as gold chains, ornaments called <hi rend="italic">Indra-gōpas,</hi> caps worked with gold, bronze plates and torches to god Raṅgarāja by Akkājamma.</p>						

						<p>The date of the record is lost. </p>						

